					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I know how memory use works through the Software level, but I want to understand it through the hardware level. What I am mainly asking is how the memory chip on the NES for example, knows that when the address bus is at $037D, it knows “Hey! That’s me!” I just assume that the chip has a predetermined address range. But if that’s the case, then why is it that when I go on eBay to buy EPROMs, it never mentions what the address range for it is?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

